                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/1584</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-28">June 28,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Australian Minister called upon me at quarter past one today, the only time I
                    had available to see him. He left with me the attached memorandum<note n="84"
                        xml:id="d401fn84">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> which he said represented the views of
                    his Government as urgently expressed to him in telegrams which he had received
                    during the past twenty-four hours.</p>
                <p>The Minister stated that he was due to see the Secretary of State, together with
                    the British Ambassador, at four o’clock this afternoon. I told the Minister I
                    would be glad to see that the Secretary had this memorandum before the
                    meeting.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
